The paper discusses a Reinforcement Learning (RL) approach to learning in environments with large state and action spaces, and sparse rewards, which is a common problem in Artificial Intelligence (AI). The paper also focuses on natural language instructions on the Web, which falls under the category of Computational Linguistics (CL). The use of deep neural networks for RL is a common approach in Machine Learning (ML), which is a subfield of AI. The paper also discusses the use of meta-learning, which is a subfield of ML. The focus on human-computer interaction (HCI) and the evaluation of the agent's ability to navigate web forms suggests that the paper may also belong to the subfield of Human-Computer Interaction (HC). Finally, the use of web forms and the evaluation on a benchmark dataset suggests that the paper may also belong to the subfield of Information Retrieval (IR).
